>
	   <a name=96670992419570></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f96670992419570><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=14&mid=96670992419570>Solo Giants</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=14&mid=96670992419570#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Aug 19th 2:32 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hiyas,<br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;I found that in Rathe Mountains I could solo Clops, Cynthia and eventually Hill Giants by using Dark followed by Venom of snake and then Invoke fear.  Starting a HP to Mana drain b4 fight allows for vamp curse during fight.  If you time it right at about 10 seconds after venom of snake wears off so will dark.  So when you see venom of snake has worn off message reapply either dooming darkness or best ye got.  <br><br>  Send pet eithr b4 dark or after you fear depending on your style.  I would dark, poison and pull to safe spot then attack pet and fear. reapply dark afterpoison runs out and then med. variation would be to reapply venom to speed up kill.  When monster was just about dead I'd cast vamp curse and med as monster die.  Can regain about 1 bub HP with CoB and vamp curse running.<br><br>Good Hunting<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
	   </form></table><ul>

</ul>
<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%>
	   <a name=9666868066178></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9666868066178><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=14&mid=9666868066178>splitting 2 mobs</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=14&mid=9666868066178#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Aug 19th 8:06 AM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>IF you have to split 2 mobs, use screaming terror, or fear to get rid of one of them, then back away from the spawn point out of aggro range, and set your pet on the second target.<br>Do this quickly and feign death.<br>Stay feigned until your terror or fear spell has worn off (on wearing off it aggros mob), and the first mob will forget about you, you can stand up and kill the mob on your pet.<br>Another way, is to darkness one of the mobs, run off with both chasing you, and feign until the darkness wears off.&nbsp;&nbsp;The darknessed mob will usually not begin to return to spawn point until after the dot wears off, while the other mob will usually wander back 10 seconds or so after you feign.<br>Make sure your pet is left in a safe area, away from the path you are leading the mobs on, and when darkness wears off, get up asap--your pet suicides after 2 minutes feigned, and upper level darkness spells tend to last about 90-100 seconds.<br>Most mobs wont remember you after feign, if there is not still one of your spell effects on them<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
	   </form></table><ul>

</ul>
<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%>
	   <a name=9666861631633></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9666861631633><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=14&mid=9666861631633>snare</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=14&mid=9666861631633#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Aug 19th 7:56 AM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Most Necros and ShadowKnights feel that darkness is a much better spell than snare.<br>I disaggree.<br>Sure there's some extra damage, but if you have someone with you who can snare, your mana is better spent on more efficient killing spells.<br>Plus Snare has the added benefit of not wearing off during battle.<br>If you are using darkness, and its dropping is gonna put you in big trouble, know how long it takes to wear off, and try to have the critter feared when it does--or buy a stopwatch and time it out exactly--you can begin casting just before it wears off, and avoid the stampede.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
	   </form></table><ul>
