	   <tr><td colspan=2>I must totally disagree with you people here. Snare is better than our darkness line. It lasts longer, gets resisted less, casts faster, takes a lot less mana, and has more of a movement reduction effect than our darkness line (snare has as much movement reduction as dooming darkness....ensnare has better than dooming). The purpose of snare is to stop the mob from flee or stop it from running faster than you. Even though our darkness line does damage, thats just a small added bonus that doesn't make up for all the things snare does over our darkness. Also, stop saying: <br><br>"necro = kick stupid dirty druids in every duel, cause snare sucks, your DoT's suck, you DD's really suck, and you basicly you suck".<br><br>I am sorry but anyone who has druids suck have a really big problem. If I ever catch you asking for sow or tp's i will have to hurt you badly. Just becuase us necromancers are really good at soloing/duels it doesn't mean we are the best. So stop thinking you are so awesome and that you can kick anyone's *ss. It is possible for a druid to beat a necro in a duel. If they know what their doing it can be done. BTW I find it highly funny that you are saying druid DD's really suck when they can DD better than us at almost all spell levels. Take your bad ideas and lame attitude out of here.<br><br>BOTTOM LINE: Druid snare is much better than necro snare, which was the whole idea of this string.<br><br>Corpusnuntia/Zuranthium/Divineshadow/Sunsong/Natalos/Naltec/Plantmaster<br><br>Player of many characters on the Nameless server.<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
