	   <tr><td colspan=2>You guys are all wrong.&nbsp;&nbsp;Why do you hotkey so many spells?  I also didnt see many /pet back off hotkeys, what do you do if your pet starts chasing something?  These are the hotkeys i use at lvl 45.<br><br>1, /pet attack<br>2, Spells (Brings you to spellbook for quick change of spells)<br>3, Sit (allows you to med during battles and keep an eye on what you are fighting)<br>4, Persona (Just a basic utility, can use the "i" key but i choose not to)<br>5, /pet back off (a out of control pet makes you unwanted in groups and messes up screaming terror)<br>6, Jboots (all necros should have them, i dont see how you can solo anything without them, they are hotkeyed for easy access incase they start to wear off during a fight)<br><br>I dont keep any spells hotkeyed because they are easily clicked on with the pointer and you wont save any time using keys.<br><br>Tiviz Contagion<br>Lvl 45 necro on luclin<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
