	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f96688812615900><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=14&mid=96688812615900>40-44 in a weekend</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=14&mid=96688812615900#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=773><span id= >BaelMT</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>3 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Aug 21st 4:02 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.33]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Although this was boring, I did rent a few movies and had fun teasing my cat. I went to the two Troll guards in Rathe Mountians and soloed them both.<br><br>Here's what you do.<br>Summon a pet till it's the best you can get. Go and buy 2 swords from the vendors right next to you, and then Augment Death him. Now sit and med till you have Full Mana, but don't use CoB lower then 3 bubs of health (EVER!) because the SK has a nasty Harm Touch. Now Pull the SK first, and pull him away from the Shaman and her dog. Pull by sending the Pet in first for that HT sponge, and then put your favorite darkness on him. I used Dooming cause it's slower and you need it. Then fear him, followed by VoS and a Life Tap. Wait about 5 seconds and drop a Vampiric Embrace on him and run over infront of the Shaman and start medding. If Fear breaks don't worry, your pet will take care of him if it's after about 15-20 seconds.<br><br>Med for 3 minutes (Don't loot), and then kill the shaman. If she has the dog then fear it first then use the same spells you used on the SK with her. After the last Dot (Vamp) is on her run and loot the SK and start medding ASAP.<br><br>I did this this weekend starting Friday with 1/2 a bub into 40. I was 44th and a bub by Sunday night and that included more then a few breaks. I also grouped with people as they came and went, but never more then 1 person. Every 4th or 5th Troll I sometimes had to med and wait for them both to spawn again, in that case kill the shaman again so she wont have the dog.<br><br><br><br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
