<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%>
	   <a name=96655151723705></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f96655151723705><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=14&mid=96655151723705>NPC Hunting: Trissa Whistlesong - Levels 12-17</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=14&mid=96655151723705#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=347><span id= >Kithias</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>12 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Aug 17th 6:31 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.16]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>After getting level 12 and the new spells/pet, head over to West Freeport and to the Hog Caller Inn (big building near the Academy of Arcane Sciences). It is the building with a brew barrel out front. Some evil races might have to Gather Shadows and sneak in, but once inside stay on the bottom floor and hang a left from the main counter. You'll come upon a square room with funky carpeting in the middle and a female merchant behind a counter. This is THE spot for necromancers 12-17.<br><br>The main NPC in this room that you&#8217;ll want to hunt is Trissa Whistlesong. She's a bard that always spawns at level 15. She'll con red at level 12 but with a good pet and all your DOTs + a few Lifetaps, she goes down easy. There is a pathing bug in this room that causes Trissa to run around the carpeting to get to you. Exploit it at your own risk, I never found the need to use it, even at 12.<br><br>While Trissa is on a 5 or so minute spawn, there is another NPC named Lady Shae that is on a 12 minute spawn. She pops on the upper floors of the inn and wanders down (don&#8217;t go up there, high level NPC with her that will kill you) to Trissa's room. She is level 12, hits for about the same as Trissa (between 15-30) but has fewer hitpoints and less AC. If you hang back at the farthest wall with tables and chairs and keep your pet back as well, she will enter the room and not aggro on you. Between levels 12-15 having both Trissa and Shae on your pet and you can easily mean death. Around 16 with the new pet and spells you don&#8217;t need to worry about it as much.<br><br>Faction. Some races are not KOS to Shae, and some are. Same with Trissa. Be sure to con while visible to find out when you see them each for the first time. Eventually if you kill them enough you will become KOS. Trissa lowers faction with: Guards of Qeynos, League of Anatonican Bards, Knights of Truth and raises faction with: Mayong Mistmoore, Ring'o'Scales. Shae lowers faction with: FelGard and a few others I believe (she is a High-Elven Paladin, don&#8217;t think you can go to Felwithe after this).<br><br>A solid plan is to time each spawn of these two and take them one at a time when you are able. That will increase the amount of experience you get quite a bit. As for loot, Shae has nothing but silver and copper and the occasional alcoholic beverage. Trissa is a different matter, and drops up to a few gold, silver, copper, and a mandolin, ALWAYS. This sells to the female merchant across the room for around 1.2 PP. Trissa occasionally drops words/runes, another mandolin, or some other bard instrument. Considering the spawn time, hanging out here for an hour or two can net you considerable money at this level.<br><br>Around 16 or 17 these two won&#8217;t give you that good experience, although you can continue to kill them to around 19 or 20 when the experience tops out. I will post further guides (and better spots) for hunting between 17-22 soon. Good hunting until then.<br>&nbsp;<br>Happy Hunting,<br>Kith</td></tr>
